service.name: Commonwealth Seniors Health Card
service.description: Commonwealth Seniors Health Card (CSHC) is currently issued to people of age pension age who: do not qualify for the pension because of income or assets, but have income below the applicable cut offs. The CSHC provides access to pharmaceuticals under the Pharmaceutical Benefits Scheme at a concessional rate.

Dimension.name: Older Australians
Dimension.desc: As an older Australian, you may be planning for retirement or have decided to work past age pension age. We have payments and services to help with your health care and living costs.

Dimension.name: Centrelink
Dimension.desc: Delivering a range of payments and services for people at times of major change.
